\Abstract{
  The \pkg{mixComp} package for \proglang{R} provides various methods of estimating the complexity of a finite mixture. While not the primary goal of the package, most methods simultaneously estimate the component weights and parameters. In this document, we give a brief overview of the methodology, and demonstrate the package's functionality in both real world examples and synthetically generated data. Moreover, we show how the package can be used on virtually any parametric mixture as long as functions generating random variates and evaluating the density are provided for the component distribution.
}

